survey [--branch B] [--window N] [--recent K] [--workload PAT] [--json] [--no-preamble]

Standing review of accumulated nightly fsperf digests: a workload TIER
TABLE (which workloads can be trusted for single-night gating vs which are
trend-only) plus a RECENT section that flags only persistent, multi-night
moves. Encodes the noise structure so it doesn't get re-derived by hand.

  --branch B       results branch (default for-next)
  --window N       trailing samples to consider (0 = all history)
  --recent K       runs shown / persistence horizon (default 5; persist=3)
  --workload PAT   glob filter on workload names
  --json           structured output for downstream tools
  --no-preamble    skip the explanatory header

See `fsperf-utils trend` for change-point detection and `fsperf-utils
evaluate` for patch-vs-baseline gating.
